      <h1 class="display-2">Fractal Ma<span class="vim-caret">n</span></h1>
      <div class="lead mb-3 text-mono text-success">RÃºben Aguiar</div>
      <p class="mt-5 text-grey text-spacey">
      Gurren is a Phoenix Server, made to learn and explore Elixir.
      Security, Performance and Scale were main focuses.
      As of now, Gurren provides a chat functionality alongside streaming of
      Microphone Audio. The goal was to make a very low latency real time stream,
      but at the moment, audio is still a bit flaky due to JS, if low levels of
      latency are wanted.
      Authentication is already implemented, even if it's currently only used to
      access certain admin pages (try <a href="<%= static_path(@conn, "/users") %>">Users</a> or <a href="<%= static_path(@conn, "/sessions") %>">Sessions</a>).
      Sessions are not yet used as part of a 2FA, but the functionality and logging
      are there, making it possible to inspect and kill compromised sessions.
      The server is currently on the AWS free tier, with a matching RDS Postgres DB.
      Terraform is used to provision and deploy at the click of a button. An haproxy
      is used on the machine to handle traffic, and SSL is enabled via
      letsencrypt (auto renew configured).
      </br>
      In the future, a Unity application (<a href="https://gitlab.com/r.aguiar9080/inner-world.git">Inner World</a>) will fully connect to this Server and
      provide p2p streaming audio capabilities on a 3D Environment.
      </p>

